{{Infobox coat of arms |name = Coat of arms of Grenada |image = Coat of arms of Grenada.svg |image_width = 250 |middle = |middle_width = |middle_caption = |lesser = |lesser_width = |lesser_caption = |armiger = [[Elizabeth II]] [[Monarchy of Grenada|in Right of Grenada]] |year_adopted = 1974 |crest = On a golden helmet affronty, lambrequined Gules, seven red roses surrounded with a garland of Bougainvillea-flowers. |torse = Argent and Gules |shield = Quarterly, a cross Or, 1&4: Gules, a lion passant guardant Or, 2&3: Vert, a crescent and a lily Or; and in nombril point a picture of the Santa Maria. |supporters = An armadillo on the dexter, supporting a stalk of maize, and a pigeon on the sinister, supporting a banana tree, all proper |compartment = [[Mount Saint Catherine (Grenada)|Mount St. Catherine]] and [[Grand Etang Lake]], all proper |motto = '''Ever Conscious of God, We Aspire, Build and Advance as One People''' |orders = |other_elements = |earlier_versions = |use = }}
The official '''coat of arms of [[Grenada]]''' is a shield divided into four parts by a golden cross. In the centre of this cross is the [[Santa María (ship)|''Santa Maria'']], [[Christopher Columbus|Columbus']] flagship.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gov.gd/coa.html |title=Coat of Arms |publisher=[[Government of Grenada]] |accessdate=2008-07-12 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080403072754/http://www.gov.gd/coa.html |archivedate=2008-04-03 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref> A British lion on a red field is shown in the upper left and lower right sections of the shield, with a golden crescent moon out of which a [[Lilium|lily]] growsin the upper right and lower left sections. Above the shield there is a golden helmet, topped with a garland of [[bougainvillea]] branches. Within the garland are seven red [[rose]]s, which stand for the seven communities of Grenada. Holding the shield on the dexter side is an [[armadillo]] which stands before a [[maize|corn]] stalk; on the sinister side is a [[Grenada dove]], which stands before a [[banana]] plant. The base represents [[Mount Saint Catherine (Grenada)|Mount St. Catherine]] with the [[Grand Etang Lake]] at the centre. A ribbon displays the national motto: "Ever conscious of God we aspire, build and advance as one people."
The coat of arms was adopted by the [[island nation]] in 1974 following independence.
